		<node ID="ID_1040703853" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Real-time_operating_system" TEXT="Real-time operating system - Wikipedia">
			<node ID="ID_1049331254" TEXT="A real-time operating system (RTOS) is an operating system (OS) intended to serve real-time applications that process data as it comes in typically without buffer delays. Processing time requirements (including any OS delay) are measured in tenths of seconds or shorter increments of time. A real-time system is a time-bound system which has well-defined fixed time constraints." />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_1131994052" LINK="https://www.studytonight.com/operating-system/types-of-os" TEXT="Types of Operating Systems | Studytonight">
